On Escalation Ticket # 00439575 the new comment has been added: Adam DeSapio:

@Michael Burrofato @Salesforce @WaitingOnEngineer @Chris Brooks

What was provided is insufficient.

The FS scan job and FS bi job logs are empty, and I requested applet logs not applet server logs.

Applet server logs are the logs for the process FSAAAppletServer.exe found in the FSAA folder with the format
FSAA_Applet_Server_[EXEC HOST]_[PID]_[DATETIME].log
whereas the Applet is FSAASrv.dll and its logs are found in the FSAA[Host] folder with the format
[FSAA/FSAC/SDD]_[HOST]_[DATETIME]_[GUID]_#.log

Please have customer change their job log levels to DEBUG at
Settings > Application > Log level > Debug (this is global)
or on the specific jobs in question rt click job > properties > Log Level > Debug.

Looks like scans are not being scoped - can we verify this?

I can only verify that the Exceptions job log and the screenshot "Host list.jpg" look the same, but
Make sure the host list is the same for scan, import, and exceptions jobs
and include the server with the missing open share (MS_DATA) in question: RCOVSVR4525.
then re-run FS scan > FS BI > Exceptions > OA.

If problem persists, please provide the new debug level job logs and applet logs.

@Michael Longo @Robert Minichino @Michael Burrofato @Salesforce @WaitingOnEngineer

The SQLite dbs for the host RCOVSVR4525 show permissions for Everyone on the share MS_DATA.
Please rule out a data collection problem by running the following in powershell, filling in the information.
$acl = Get-Acl -Path "\RCOVSVR4525MS_DATA"
$acl.Access | % { echo $_ }

You will need elevated permissions for this.
This will show if/what permissions Everyone has.
If IdentityReference: Everyone has AccessControlType:Allow, then there is no issue here and product is working as expected.
Otherwise, please provide output and we will investigate data collection.
